cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper deals with an iterative algorithm for identifying a linear subspace from partial observations of random vectors. This is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning and data analysis, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses convergence properties and assumptions on randomness, which are topics related to numerical analysis and optimization, covered by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the algorithm is related to incremental SVD methods and gradient projection algorithms, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms, covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the incoherence of the subspace with the coordinate directions, which is a topic related to signal processing and information theory, covered by cs.SI (Signal Processing).
